description: Graphify knowledge graph first. Use before grep/read.
globs: []
alwaysApply: true
---

[FILE] graphify.mdc
[OBJ] Knowledge graph orientation rule.
[RULES]
1. [REQ] If `graphify-out/graph.json` exists, use graphify BEFORE raw grep/read.
2. [CMD] `graphify query "<question>"` for architecture/codebase questions.
3. [CMD] `graphify path "<A>" "<B>"` for dependency paths.
4. [CMD] `graphify explain "<concept>"` for related concepts.
5. [REQ] Include this rule in every subagent prompt doing code exploration.
6. [CMD] If `graphify-out/wiki/index.md` exists, navigate it.
7. [CMD] Read `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` only when query/path/explain fail.
8. [CMD] Run `graphify update .` after any code edit.
